To develop mobile application, three approaches can be used. Which approach to select is depending on the timeline and budget.
The first one is using "Phone gap" or "Cordova". This tool can be used for mainly prototype of mobile app. Even though this isn't look like nativbe application, you can quickly deliver it on multiple platform.
The second approach is using "Titanium Appcelerator" and "Xamarin" Through there tools, you can quickly develop native look like mobile app. 
The last one is developing native application. This apporach is the most expensive approach amonng these three approaches. But you can get absolutely best performance and easies way to update the application. 
